name: Santa Maria de Montserrat Abbey
description: Mountain monastery with a vast basilica, iconic virgin sculpture & a museum with world renowned art.

name: Alcázar de Segovia
description: Romantic medieval castle restored after fire with ornately decorated rooms & an armoury museum.
address: Pl. Reina Victoria Eugenia, s/n, 40003 Segovia, Spain

name: Doñana National Park
description: Vast nature reserve & wetland ecosystem with lynx plus nesting & breeding sites for migratory birds.

name: Teatro Romano de Mérida
description: Hilltop remains of a Roman arena & waiting rooms used for gladiator & animal fights.
address: Plaza Margarita Xirgu, s/n, 06800 Mérida, Badajoz, Spain

name: Timanfaya National Park
description: Park with regulated public access by camel, on foot or by coach tour, plus a geothermal restaurant.

name: Las Médulas
description: Expansive Roman gold mine amid craggy red rocks, with cave tours, tunnels & archaeological museum.

name: Bardenas Reales
description: Soaring canyons, sandstone cliffs & rocky outcrops are the draw to this sprawling desert region.

name: Isola Bella
description: Ferries travel to this tiny island featuring an ornate palace, Italianate garden & fishing village.
address: Isola Bella, 28838 Stresa, Province of Verbano-Cusio-Ossola, Italy

name: Lipari
description: Small volcanic island with beaches & ancient fort ruins, plus dining, lodging & scenic views.
address: Lipari, 98050 Lipari, Metropolitan City of Messina, Italy

name: Castel del Monte
description: Unique octagonal castle built on a hill in the 13th century, with guided tours & a gift shop.

name: Parco Nazionale delle Dolomiti Bellunesi
description: Vast mountain & forest nature reserve for hiking, biking, winter sports & wildlife watching.

name: Parco Nazionale Gran Paradiso
description: Protected land offering hiking paths, wildlife, an alpine botanic garden & visitor centers.
